body:
This PR ads MLIR pass plugin functionality to firtool pipeline to dynamically load pass plugins and execute passes. https://github.com/uenoku/firtool-standalone-plugin provides a plugin example (`standalone-switch-bar-foo` pass) and firtool can dynamically load the plugin there. Still not sure it's worth adding the plugin mechanism because of the complexity added though. Currently I added `-low-firrtl-pass-plugin` option that injects passes before LowerToHW. 


Example:
```
$ cat foo.fir
circuit Bar: %[[
  { "target": "~Bar|Bar>bar", "class": "firrtl.transforms.DontTouchAnnotation"}
]]
  module Bar:
    input w: UInt<1>
    wire bar:UInt<1>
    
    bar <= w

$ firtool foo.fir
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.56.1-118-g195ae0749
module Bar(
  input w
);

  wire bar = w;
endmodule

$ firtool foo.fir -load-pass-plugin=<firtool-standalone-plugin>/build/lib/StandalonePlugin.so -low-firrtl-pass-plugin='firrtl.circuit(standalone-switch-bar-foo)'
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.56.1-118-g195ae0749
module Bar(
  input w
);

  wire foo = w;
endmodule
```

Related to https://github.com/llvm/circt/issues/4933
